## C1 Decision Engine: Figma Image Checklist

All images should be abstract/conceptual — no real product data. Export PNG at 2x. Save to `/static/projects/images/` using `c1-decision-engine-[descriptor].png`.

**Product structure for reference:**
- **Onboarding wizard** (setup): Step 1 (outcome type) → Step 2 (name + description) → Step 3 (pick data elements via split panel)
- **Main interface** (core product): Rules data table — each row is a policy rule: Rule Name | If this (data element badge) | Operator | Amount | Outcome. Toolbar has Bulk actions, Test model, and Add rule.

---

- [ ] **Hero image** (`c1-decision-engine-hero.png`) — The main rules data table with 3–4 rows populated. Show the full toolbar (Bulk actions, Test model, Add rule) and the column headers (Rule Name, If this, Operator, Amount, Outcome). Use placeholder rule names and abstract data element badges. This is the core product.

- [ ] **Rule row anatomy** (`c1-decision-engine-rule-row-anatomy.png`) — A single rule row, zoomed and annotated with callout labels: drag handle, rule name input, data element badge ("If this"), operator selector, amount field, outcome column. This is the "rule cell" described in the case study — most important image.

- [ ] **Onboarding flow** (`c1-decision-engine-onboarding-flow.png`) — All three wizard steps shown in sequence (stacked or side-by-side): Step 1 outcome radio group, Step 2 name/description form, Step 3 data element split panel. Shows the structured setup progression before reaching the main interface.

- [ ] **Data element selector detail** (`c1-decision-engine-data-element-selector.png`) — Zoomed view of the Step 3 split panel: searchable list with a few items checked on the left, metadata preview (description, datatype, attribute path) on the right. Shows how data complexity is surfaced clearly.

- [ ] **Before/after** (`c1-decision-engine-before-after.png`) — Left: a messy spreadsheet grid with scattered policy logic (multiple tabs, no structure). Right: the clean rules table with consistent row structure. Keep diagrammatic — doesn't need to be pixel-perfect.

